parameters.text:
** DATA WILL BE UPDATED AS A PART OF THE REGULAR REFRESH BY MID AUGUST **
"Core Premier (A la Carte) & Priority" & "Signature" are included in  "☁ Total" 
Customer = regional parent company excluding non-profit and zero-AOV customers
Addressable Market = Market size defined by Gartner/SFDC and does not sum across sub-products. Marketshare = AOV / Total Addressable Market.
Red Accounts: Account escalations that represent attriton risk (AOV)
> Red accounts tied to platform suitability/overall performance allocated to Other L2 Product category. 
> Red accounts associated with MC platform/stability issues allocated to "Messaging/journeys" at Level 2 Product

"Core Premier (A la Carte) & Priority" & "Signature" are included in  "☁ Total" 
ACV: Availability of information in org62 can effect historical trends.
AOV: Availability of information in org62 can effect historical trends
Attrition: Trailing 12 months (TTM) attrition. Core only prior to FY15Q1. FY18 total attrition reflects SFDC excluding CC, Krux, and Heroku online business
** ATTRITION DATA AS OF SEPTEMBER FY19
Pipeline: Pipe numbers exclude CSG pipePipe Gen = Sum of $ amount of opportunities that moved to Stage 2. Note: Core pipe gen includes Premiere a-la-carte. The rest of CSG pipe gen is reported within CSG cut.

** DATA (T&P Cost to Serve, Availability% and Transactions/requests) WILL BE UPDATED AS A PART OF THE REGULAR REFRESH BY MID AUGUST **
"Core Premier (A la Carte) & Priority" & "Signature" are included in  "☁ Total"
SWE = Software Engineering IC's. Excludes SWE's Product Trust and Infra that are not working on product.
Infra: Represents total HC in the infrastructure organization
T&P Cost to Serve: Includes Infra, 3rd party royalty, and R&D + Products. Metric has 1 quarter lag (Q4 numbers are indicative of Q3 ending)
Availability %: Reflects core data centers onlyCPM total reflects core data centers only. Availability for sub-products may reflect total core data centers as well.

"Core Premier (A la Carte) & Priority" & "Signature" are included in  "☁ Total" 
Within the AE, Co Prime, SE sections, % columns 3 & 4 represent 24 month CAGR (quarterly and YTD)
AEs: Includes ECS, Marketing Cloud (Messaging/Journies), and Commerce Cloud AE's
SEs: Excludes Q Branch, Spark, IPD, and SE Management
Co Prime: CSG Coprime = APs (account partners) that worked through the Qtr
AE Participation: Totals not shown and metric is only broken out by the cloud dimensions.
